Package: drawYpath
Type: Package
Title: A shiny app to manually find trajectories in data.
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Marc-Antoine GERAULT
Maintainer: Marc-Antoine GERAULT <marco.gerault@gmail.com>
Description: This package contains a shiny app that allow the user to draw path on a plot thanks to plotly.
     Then, it finds the points next to this path and plot a heatmap of those points.
     This app can be useful when the user want to find its own trajectories, to keep a more biological view
     than just  use an algorithm.
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0),
         shiny (>= 1.7.1),
         plotly (>= 4.10.0),
         ggplot2 (>= 3.3.4)
Imports: shiny, shinydashboard, plotly, ggplot2, ggplotify, pheatmap, stringr, tidyverse
Suggests: EBImage
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
